  "body": "It would be great if React could support the following API (or would allow to write an extension):\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\nimport {animate} from 'react';\r\nimport d3 from 'd3';\r\n\r\nfunction Chart(props) {\r\n  return (\r\n    <svg>\r\n      <rect\r\n        width={animate(props.width).duration(500).easing('in-out')}\r\n        style={{\r\n          fill: animate(props.color).interpolate(d3.interpolateRgb),\r\n          opacity: animate().initial(1).remove(0), // animate how element disappears\r\n        }}\r\n      />\r\n      <polygon points={animate(d3.polygon(props.points)).interpolate(d3.interpolate)} />\r\n    </svg>\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently this is implemented in a simple [Maleviƒç.js](https://github.com/alexanderby/malevic) library (`.remove()` not implemented yet). See the live [example](https://codepen.io/shutovby/pen/GYzjvj).",
